HEADWORD: Furlong
<hw>Fur"long</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>furlong</ets>, <ets>furlang</ets>, AS. <ets>furlang</ets>,
<ets>furlung</ets>, prop., the length of a furrow; <ets>furh</ets>
furrow + <ets>lang</ets> long. See <er>Furrow</er>, and <er>Long</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <def>A measure of length; the eighth part of a
mile; forty rods; two hundred and twenty yards.</def>⟦br⟧
